Between January 23 and February 16, 2019, a total of 13 human cases of laboratory-confirmed MERS-CoV were reported in Oman [Fig. 1
]. Nine cases (69%) were residents of North Al Batinah, and four cases (31%) were from South Ash Sharqiyah Governorates (23) [Fig. 2
]. Eleven cases (85%) were Omani nationals.
